spanGrp.span: There were times when we were already forgetting this language.
elä gäldi period uže biz bu dili unudirdıh uže
Because we all studied in Russian at school then when we went to Russia and entered into the institute, we continued studying in Russian.
onučun ki biz ohuduh ruski urus dilındä školada sorarda gettıh urusetä instituta girdıh urusča ohuduh
I was working as an agronomist at record keeping of this area and dealing with every paper in Russian.
burda bän išlirdım agranom sortoviučastokta delopraizvodstvada äp käğıdi_mäğıdi yazerdıh urus dilındän
That’s why we don’t see the big difference between our language and Russian.
onučunda biz čoğ atličia vermerıh bizım dilınän urusčai
For us Russian is I don’t know, it’s our mother tongue.
urusča bizä bülmäm očen šei yazıktır yahši yazıktır radnoi yazık da
We have learnt this language with what we communicate at home from our parents and we speak it at home..
ävdän bu dili ävdän anamızdan babamızdan örgändıh ambu dili angısiinanki ävdä ğonuširih
And we communicate in it till now.
By the way I think that this language becomes a bit more necessary and I want children to know it.
meždu pročim šindi biräz bu dil desäm ilärlir ušahlarda istirıh bülälär šei edälär
When the communication with Turkey became better, they were coming and we were going there.
